# FoodOrderV1 — Cursor rules

# Governance-Version: 1

# Canonical truth: AGENTS.md. Then read .ai/BOOTSTRAP.md, resolve task context, and follow the matching skills/ and rules/ documents.

## Hard rules

- One-way architecture: src/app → src/modules/* → src/shared|src/platform → src/packages → vendor.
- Feature behavior lives in exactly one module and crosses modules only through public surfaces.
- Vendor packages import only inside their registered src/packages/<name> owner facade.
- Hooks only in *.hook.ts files or hooks/; *.component.tsx files call zero hooks; containers call project hooks only.
- Browser globals only in src/platform; environment reads only in src/platform/environment.
- Absolute route strings only in routes/ ownership files.
- Kebab-case filenames with truthful responsibility suffixes.
- TypeScript enum is banned; use typed as-const objects and derived unions.
- Domain constants, interfaces, types, helpers, validators, state machines, adapters, and contracts must live in truthful files; never hide them inline in screens or giant hooks.
- No global store or server-state query library.
- Complete English/Arabic copy, RTL, dark mode, accessibility, privacy, and offline/error states are required.
- Never weaken Firestore/Storage rules, auth, ownership, tests, coverage, migration safety, or rollback readiness.
- .ai/ is generated — never hand-edit.
- When a rule fails, move or redesign the code. Do not disable the rule.

## Version branches

For X.Y.Z, release/X.Y.Z, or X.Y.Z/<feature> branches, follow skills/start-version-branch.md. Source, Functions, Android, changelog, and release notes must match before commit or push. Every green branch push produces a unique checksum-verified prerelease APK; CI never commits recursive version bumps.

## Validation

- npm run release:branch-check
- npm run lint:fix && git diff --exit-code && npm run lint
- npm run typecheck && npm run typecheck:tsc
- npm run test && npm run test:coverage && npm run build
- npm run quality:circular && npm run quality:dead-code && npm run quality:release
- npm run test:e2e && npm run test:e2e:critical && npm run test:e2e:cross-browser
- npm run test:rules and npm run functions:validate when their boundaries change
- npm run knowledge:build:incremental && npm run knowledge:validate
- Conventional commits; never bypass Husky or claim unexecuted gates.
